{"title":"Online Metronome with Advanced Settings","description":"Free online metronome with advanced settings, including a choice of beats per minute, custom sounds and nice design.","content":"## What is a metronome for?\r\n\r\nA metronome is a device that plays a sound at regular intervals.\r\nIn real life, a metronome is a mechanical device in the shape of a pyramid, with a pendulum mounted on one side.\r\n\r\nWith the development of technology, many similar devices began to be presented in electronic form. Now it is not necessary to buy a separate metronome when you can use its online version. In addition to the main function of such a device as a metronome, it also has advanced functionality that will allow you to get the most out of using a metronome.\r\n\r\nThis metronome also allows you to adjust the number of beats per minute (BPM - beats per minute), sound and visual design.\r\n\r\n## Metronome functionality\r\n\r\n1. Multiple metronome configurations can be saved;\r\n2. You can set different sound for tick;\r\n3. For the metronome, it is possible to change the frequency of the tick operation;\r\n4. Setting your own sound.\r\n\r\n## Who needs a metronome?\r\nInterval metronome sounds help musicians maintain the correct tempo while playing musical instruments.\r\n\r\n## How to use the metronome?\r\n\r\nTo turn on the meronome, press the `â–¶` button.\r\nTurning on the metronome will start a cycle that will turn on all the sounds specified in the settings in sequence.\r\nYou can also create multiple customized options - they will all be saved in the browser's memory, after which they can be reused at another time."}